{"cursor":"9906","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox person\n| image = boodee K.jpg imagesize = 280px caption = Boodee Keerthisena birth_date\n| = August 11 birth_place = Sri Lanka nationality = Sri Lankan birth_name =\n| Vishvanath Buddhika Keerthisena spouse = children = occupation = Actor,\n| Director, Producer, Screenwriter, Editor, Composer, Dress designer\n| notable_works = Mille Soya, Matha influences = John Cassavetes education =\n| School Of Visual Arts (BFA FILM) alma_mater = religion = networth =\n| years_active = 1986âpresent\n}}\n\n'Vishvanath Buddhika Keerthisena', also known as 'Boodee Keerthisena' is an\naward winning Sri Lankan filmmaker. He is well known as an artist began his\ncareer with drawing comics. Quietly he moved into painting, dress designing and\nvisual arts and into music in the late 80s. He performed in a band called \"Boo-\nDee and the Woo-Zees\" ( 1986â1992 ) as the lead singer.\n\nIn 1987, he went to New York to study film. He joined the film department to\nstudy film and television at the School of Visual Arts in Manhattan. For his\ngraduation in 1995, he presented his feature film \"Veils of Maya\" (Sihina\nDeshayen - 1993 ) as his thesis. The film won 31 awards in many festivals\nincluding best director and best film.\n\nIn 1997 he started shooting \"Buongiorno Italia\" (Mille Soya) and completed its\nshooting in Sri Lanka and Italy with a crew from 8 different countries. The film\nwas released in 2004 and was in 16 festivals and won 15 awards including best\npicture and best director.\n\nIn 2008 he co-wrote the screenplay and directed \"Alone in A Valley\" (Nimnayaka\nHudakalawa)which is in post production currently.\n\nFrom 2009-2010 he directed \"Matha\", a film based on the last Elam war that ended\nafter nearly 30 years. The film was released in January 2012.\n\nSince he got back to Sri Lanka in 1995, he has directed and produced over 100 TV\ncommercials, more than 30 documentaries, Two TV series and many music videos.\n\nHis work is influenced by John Cassavetes and contains elements of \"cinema-\nverite\" style. http://www.asiaticafilmmediale.it/2001/uk2001/directors/keer-\nthisena.html\n","linknr":123,"url":"Boodee_Keerthisena","recorded":1375086190,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Boodee_Keerthisena&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Boodee_Keerthisena&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Boodee_K.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2c/Boodee_K.jpg/280px-Boodee_K.jpg","/wiki/Sri_Lanka","/wiki/School_of_Visual_Arts","/wiki/John_Cassavetes","#cite_note-1","#Filmography","#TV_Series","#TV_Commercials","#Documentaries","#Awards","#Screenplays_yet_to_be_produced","#Special","#References","#External_links","/w/index.php?title=Boodee_Keerthisena&action=edit&section=1","#cite_note-2","/w/index.php?title=Boodee_Keerthisena&action=edit&section=2","#cite_note-3","/w/index.php?title=Boodee_Keerthisena&action=edit&section=3","/w/index.php?title=Boodee_Keerthisena&action=edit&section=4","/w/index.php?title=Boodee_Keerthisena&action=edit&section=5","/wiki/Presidential_Film_Awards","/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed","/w/index.php?title=Boodee_Keerthisena&action=edit&section=6","